            "answer_text": "In Africa: Angola, Mozambique (Mo\u00e7ambique), Guinea-Bissau (Guin\u00e9-Bissau), Cape Verde (Cabo Verde), S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 & Pr\u00edncipe [literally Saint Thomas & Prince]. In South America: Brazil (Brasil). In Asia (India): Goa, Daman (Dam\u00e3o) & Diu. In Oceania/Australia: East Timor (Timor-Leste). In Asia (China): Macau was a so-called colony, but could be better called a territory under portuguese administration. So, if we include the European mainland, there were portuguese territories in the 5 continents of the world (if we count North & South America as one, and not including Antarctica). ",
